Emit ToolCallStart on the first chunk of each tool call. Per backend-spec.md §6.5.

LiteLLM streams tool calls as `chunk.choices[0].delta.tool_calls: list[ToolCallDelta]`. The id and name are usually only on the first delta. Track buffer state per tool_call_id:

  tool_buffers: dict[str, dict] = {}
  for tc_delta in chunk.choices[0].delta.tool_calls or []:
      tcid = tc_delta.id or last_seen_id
      if tcid not in tool_buffers:
          tool_buffers[tcid] = {"name": tc_delta.function.name, "args_str": ""}
          yield to_sse(ToolCallStart(tool_call_id=tcid, tool_name=tc_delta.function.name))

